<TITLE> Drizzles to continue across the country </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 27 (bdnews24.com)  The sun shone briefly through the cloudy Dhaka sky Sunday morning. The weather office in a bulletin said drizzles are likely to occur Sunday in parts of Khulna, Barisal and Chittagong divisions. One or two places in Dhaka, Rajshahi and Sylhet divisions will also experience drizzles, the Meteorological Department said in a 9am-forecast. Drizzles may continue through one or two days across the country, it said. The weather office forecast another cold spell in a couple of days. Maritime ports have been asked to show local cautionary signal-3 as clouds have formed over the Bay of Bengal, weather forecaster Abdur Rahman said. The river ports of Dhaka and southern regions have been asked to show river cautionary signal-2, he said. The northern region has improved, as less rainfall has been recorded, but the temperature may decrease, the Met office said. The lowest temperature in Dhaka for Sunday was recorded at 13.7 degrees Celsius, the bulletin said. bdnews24.
